 r.m.s. field (or magnetic\nenergy). In the limit of small Reynolds numbers ($\\eta, \\ \\nu \\rightarrow\n\\infty$), the dynamo behavior is related to the well-known alpha--omega {\\it\nansatz} when the forcing is steady ($t_f \\rightarrow \\infty$) and to the\n\"incoherent\" alpha--omega {\\it ansatz} when the forcing is purely fluctuating.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Sep 2011 20:00:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 12 Oct 2011 22:51:31 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-30"}
